text: Koombooloomba Hydro Power Station is a hydroelectric power station at Koombooloomba Dam, Queensland, Australia. Koombooloomba has one turbo generator, with a generating capacity of of electricity. The power station is owned by Stanwell Corporation. The power station was commissioned in 1999, capturing energy from existing water releases required for the operation of Kareeya Hydro Power Station. ==See also== *List of power stations in Queensland ==References== ==External links== * Clean Energy Council Category:Energy infrastructure completed in 1999 Category:Hydroelectric power stations in Queensland Category:Buildings and structures in Far North Queensland Category:1999 establishments in Australia
